After removing cloning of origin from carrier the bug did not reproduce.\r\n\r\nTo reproduce issue here is code snippet (need to use dump):\r\n```ruby\r\nuser=User.find_by(email: \"brian@worthingtondirect.com\")\r\nActsAsTenant.current_tenant = user\r\ntarget_scope_map = Ratesmgr::ScopeMapper.find_by_master_scope(\"TEST\")\r\nRequestStore.store[:scope_mgmt_new_scope] = target_scope_map.scope\r\nRatesmgr::Origin.find(37686).amoeba_dup.save\r\n``` \r\n\r\nOr longer one, the whole scope copy:\r\n```ruby\r\nuser=User.find_by(email: \"brian@worthingtondirect.com\") \r\nActsAsTenant.current_tenant = user\r\nsource=\"LIVE\"\r\ntarget=\"TEST\"\r\nsource_scope_map = Ratesmgr::ScopeMapper.find_by_master_scope(source)\r\ntarget_scope_map = Ratesmgr::ScopeMapper.find_by_master_scope(target)\r\ncommand = ScopeManagement::Duplicate.new(source_scope_map.scope, target_scope_map.scope, [])\r\ncommand.execute\r\n```",
